import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    zip_code_counts = data['zip_code'].value_counts()
    zip_code_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Zip Codes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes in the dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Group data by county and count data points
    county_data = data.groupby('county').size().reset_index(name='count')
    
    # Load US counties shapefile
    counties = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datablist/us-counties/master/us-counties.geojson')
    
    # Merge data with shapefile
    merged_data = counties.merge(county_data, left_on='NAME', right_on='county')
    
    # Plot choropleth map
    merged_data.plot(column='count', cmap='coolwarm', legend=True, figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.title('Which counties have the highest concentration of data points?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
